    {
      "directory": ".",
      "description": "# üîê Step 1: Create Your API Token\n\n**You'll need an API token to manage your Okta organization.**\n\n**To create your API token:**\n1. **From the Okta Admin console, go to** Security ‚Üí API ‚Üí Tokens tab\n2. **Click:** \"Create Token\"\n3. **Name it:** \"Terraform Racing Lab\"\n4. **Set IP restrictions:** Select \"Any IP\" (for lab purposes)\n5. **Click:** \"Create Token\"\n6. **COPY THE TOKEN IMMEDIATELY** - you won't see it again! (We'll use this in the next step so you don't need to worry about pasting it anywhere just yet.)\n\n**‚ö†Ô∏è Important:** Keep this token safe - it's like the keys to your racing team headquarters!"
    },
    {
      "directory": ".",
      "description": "# üîß Step 2: Store Your Secrets Securely\n\n**GitHub Codespaces provides secure secret storage for your API credentials.**\n\n**Set up your Codespace secrets:**\n1. **Open:** [GitHub Codespaces Secrets](https://github.com/settings/codespaces)\n2. **Click:** \"New secret\" and create these **3 secrets**:\n\n| Secret Name | Value | Your Example |\n|-------------|-------|--------------|\n| `OKTA_ORG_NAME` | **JUST the org name** (before .oktapreview.com) | `dev-123456` |\n| `OKTA_BASE_URL` | Your base URL | `oktapreview.com` |\n| `OKTA_API_TOKEN` | Your API token from Step 1 | `00abc123def456...` |\n\n**‚ö†Ô∏è Important for OKTA_ORG_NAME:**\n- ‚úÖ **Correct:** `dev-123456` or `oktaicedev002112`\n- ‚ùå **Wrong:** `dev-123456.oktapreview.com` or `https://dev-123456.oktapreview.com`\n\n3. **For each secret:** Select this repository in \"Repository access\"\n4. **Restart your Codespace** to load the secrets\n\n**üîí Why this way?** Keeps credentials secure and out of your code!"
    },
    {
      "directory": ".",
      "description": "‚úÖ Step 3: Verify Your Environment\n\nLet's make sure that your codespace can see the variables you just set.  Run the following command to check your environment variables:\n\n```bash\necho \"Org Name: $OKTA_ORG_NAME; echo Base URL: $OKTA_BASE_URL; echo API Token: ${OKTA_API_TOKEN:0:8}...\" && echo \"Token loaded: $(if [ -n \"$OKTA_API_TOKEN\" ]; then echo 'Yes'; else echo 'No'; fi)\"\n```\n\n**Expected output:**\n- Org Name: dev-12345 (your org)\n- Base URL: oktapreview.com\n- Token loaded: Yes\n\n‚ùå If any are missing: Your secrets aren't loaded - check that you completed the previous step, and restart your Codespace!"
