      },
      "description": "# üîß Terraform Configuration Block\n\nThis is like the technical regulations for our racing series! The `terraform` block defines:\n\n- **Required version**: Minimum Terraform version needed\n- **Required providers**: External plugins that extend Terraform's capabilities\n\n**For broader infrastructure:** If we wanted to manage AWS, Azure, or other services alongside Okta, we'd add their providers here too. But since this lab focuses on identity management, Okta is our only provider.\n\n When we run `terraform init`, Terraform will download the specified providers from Hashicorp's provider registry. Providers are how Terraform learns about different resource types, like Okta groups and Okta users. When you have questions about a resource, check the documentation of the provider that it comes from."
    },
