      "description": "# üîê Provider Configuration\n\nThe `provider` block is like connecting to race control - it establishes communication with Okta's API.\n\n**Security Note**: We use secrets stored in environment variables for this lab, which you configured in an earlier step:\n- `OKTA_ORG_NAME` - Your organization name\n- `OKTA_BASE_URL` - oktapreview.com\n- `OKTA_API_TOKEN` - Your API authentication token\n\n **In production environments:** If you're using Terraform at your company, talk to your DevOps or platform teams! If they're using Terraform already, they'll have established patterns for secrets management (like HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, or Azure Key Vault) that you should follow."
