      },
      "description": "# üèÅ Racing Teams Module\n\n Under the hood, Terraform uses your API token to make API calls to examine the current state of your Okta organization and make changes. This can cause rate limit problems as you manage more resources. Modules can help you group resources that change together. This lets Terraform get work done while making as few API calls as possible, like how engineers build race cars to have only the parts they need!   \n\n**Key concepts:**\n- **Modules** organize related resources together\n- **Source** points to our local module directory\n- **Input variables** pass data to the module\n- **Reusability** - modules can be used in different configurations\n\nThis is how real companies structure their Terraform code! üèóÔ∏è"
    },
