      "description": "# üèéÔ∏è Racing Drivers Module (Conditional)\n\n**Advanced pattern:** Conditional module deployment! Sometimes checking a variable and changing Terraform's behavior as a result can be helpful. But Terraform is not the place to do complex logic about what to deploy. If you find yourself using a lot of conditionals like this in your Terraform, step back and consider whether there's a better place in your deployment architecture to keep that logic. \n\n**Key features:**\n- `count = var.enable_drivers ? 1 : 0` - Deploy only when enabled\n- **Module dependencies** - drivers module uses outputs from teams module\n- **Progressive deployment** - deploy teams first, then drivers\n\n**Where are those variables coming from?** We'll configure them soon!"
    },
