      "description": "# üìù Create Your Configuration File\n\n**terraform.tfvars** stores the **values** of the variables we're using. \n\n**Let's create your `terraform.tfvars` file:**\n\n**Option 1 - Command line:** Select [this link](command:codetour.sendTextToTerminal?[\"cp terraform.tfvars.example terraform.tfvars\"]) to copy the example file.\n\n**Option 2 - VS Code interface:**\n1. Right-click on `terraform.tfvars.example` in the file explorer (left sidebar)\n2. Select \"Copy\"\n3. Right-click in empty space ‚Üí \"Paste\" ‚Üí Rename to `terraform.tfvars`\n\n**Find `terraform.tfvars` in the left sidebar.** This is where Terraform will look to see what value it should use whenever you refer to a variable."
